1
00:01:26,680 --> 00:01:27,400
Yiyi,

2
00:01:29,080 --> 00:01:30,240
will this work?

3
00:01:31,240 --> 00:01:32,960
Could he have gone into the TV?

4
00:01:37,520 --> 00:01:39,520
Almost there. Let's go.

5
00:02:05,880 --> 00:02:07,340
Do your words still count?

6
00:02:07,920 --> 00:02:09,120
What did I say?

7
00:02:09,320 --> 00:02:09,840
Didn't you say

8
00:02:09,840 --> 00:02:11,760
you found a way to send me back?

9
00:02:12,960 --> 00:02:15,680
Oh, let me relax and rest a bit.

10
00:02:16,360 --> 00:02:18,400
But I still have supplies to deliver,

11
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:19,800
and it's been so many days.

12
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:21,530
You should have found it by now.

13
00:02:23,960 --> 00:02:25,520
Don't rush me.

14
00:02:25,760 --> 00:02:26,440
I...

15
00:02:26,440 --> 00:02:28,440
This is my first time doing this.

16
00:02:28,720 --> 00:02:29,880
I've searched for so many days,

17
00:02:29,880 --> 00:02:30,880
watched so many shows,

18
00:02:30,880 --> 00:02:32,320
and looked up so much information.

19
00:02:32,320 --> 00:02:33,200
I'm not a god,

20
00:02:33,200 --> 00:02:33,920
right?

21
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:34,860
How about this,

22
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:36,520
give me a little more time

23
00:02:36,680 --> 00:02:37,680
to relax,

24
00:02:37,680 --> 00:02:38,760
play some games,

25
00:02:38,760 --> 00:02:39,760
and clear my mind.

26
00:02:40,960 --> 00:02:41,880
And you,

27
00:02:43,320 --> 00:02:44,850
just read a book for a while.

28
00:02:45,600 --> 00:02:47,329
Are you sure he can understand?

29
00:02:48,880 --> 00:02:49,520
Right.

30
00:02:49,880 --> 00:02:50,680
I forgot

31
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:53,480
you can't read simplified characters.

32
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:55,040
But

33
00:02:55,040 --> 00:02:57,320
it's not entirely incomprehensible, right?

34
00:02:57,320 --> 00:02:58,920
You can guess while reading,

35
00:02:59,120 --> 00:03:00,320
like a puzzle.

36
00:03:03,920 --> 00:03:05,200
Guess while reading?

37
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:17,800
How do I read this?

38
00:03:17,880 --> 00:03:18,880
Swipe it.

39
00:03:44,040 --> 00:03:44,800
Yiyi,

40
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:45,640
this book,

41
00:03:45,640 --> 00:03:47,640
I really can't read some words in it.

42
00:03:47,680 --> 00:03:49,120
Why don't you figure something out

43
00:03:49,120 --> 00:03:49,920
and see if

44
00:03:50,280 --> 00:03:52,480
you can send me back as soon as possible?

45
00:03:54,079 --> 00:03:56,079
I almost forgot about you.

46
00:03:58,160 --> 00:04:00,760
You can't read, but you can understand, right?

47
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:05,360
Old antique.

48
00:04:05,680 --> 00:04:07,880
I'll give you an immersive experience.

49
00:04:08,160 --> 00:04:09,490
Immersive experience?

50
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:11,680
Where are you taking me?

51
00:04:12,280 --> 00:04:14,280
Anywhere you want to go.

52
00:04:18,880 --> 00:04:20,279
Put this on first.

53
00:04:29,200 --> 00:04:30,480
My earphones.

54
00:04:30,560 --> 00:04:31,760
What are you doing?

55
00:04:32,880 --> 00:04:34,409
Yiyi, stop messing around.

56
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:36,400
The old antique can't handle it.

57
00:04:37,400 --> 00:04:38,320
I don't care.

58
00:04:38,320 --> 00:04:40,200
Your rent is doubled.

59
00:04:41,080 --> 00:04:42,610
Yaoyao, you do it yourself.

60
00:04:43,080 --> 00:04:44,200
Yiyi, your phone.

61
00:04:44,520 --> 00:04:45,850
I don't want it anymore.

62
00:04:45,960 --> 00:04:47,080
Play it for him.

63
00:04:52,440 --> 00:04:53,970
It's okay. Don't be afraid.

64
00:04:59,159 --> 00:05:00,400
These are earphones.

65
00:05:01,160 --> 00:05:02,600
They make sounds.

66
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:04,880
It gives an immersive feeling.

67
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:06,960
You can try it.

68
00:05:11,880 --> 00:05:13,080
I'll put it on for you.

69
00:05:19,480 --> 00:05:20,160
Here.

70
00:06:08,280 --> 00:06:09,480
Yes.

71
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:10,720
You can watch TV.

72
00:06:13,080 --> 00:06:14,480
Hey, Lin Yaozu.

73
00:06:14,680 --> 00:06:15,360
Yaozu.

74
00:06:15,680 --> 00:06:16,400
Yaozu.

75
00:06:17,960 --> 00:06:19,620
I'll teach you how to watch TV.

76
00:06:22,280 --> 00:06:23,280
Watch TV.

77
00:06:23,680 --> 00:06:24,320
Come here,

78
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:25,440
I'll teach you.

79
00:06:25,440 --> 00:06:26,320
Look.

80
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:27,940
This is the select button.

81
00:06:28,360 --> 00:06:30,360
You can choose the program you want to watch.

82
00:06:30,360 --> 00:06:32,020
And this is the volume button.

83
00:06:32,080 --> 00:06:33,540
You can adjust the volume.

84
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:35,400
You try.

85
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:44,600
You're the best. You arranged everything perfectly.

86
00:06:54,960 --> 00:06:56,880
Finally free.

87
00:06:57,240 --> 00:07:01,160
I never thought the TV, which has become a decoration, would be turned on one day.

88
00:07:01,160 --> 00:07:02,160
If this still doesn't work,

89
00:07:02,160 --> 00:07:04,480
I really can't keep acting.

90
00:07:05,440 --> 00:07:06,480
Director Zhang,

91
00:07:06,480 --> 00:07:07,960
your acting is amazing.

92
00:07:09,640 --> 00:07:11,880
We need some time to ourselves.

93
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:31,200
Yiyi,

94
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:33,280
why don't you guys think of a way

95
00:07:33,280 --> 00:07:34,480
to send me back first?

96
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:35,320
I have important tasks.

97
00:07:35,320 --> 00:07:36,520
I'm really in a hurry.

98
00:07:36,880 --> 00:07:38,000
Azu,

99
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:39,960
stop it.

100
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:41,960
Don't worry,

101
00:07:42,159 --> 00:07:43,600
we will send you back.

102
00:07:44,080 --> 00:07:46,240
The things you are anxious about have been solved.

103
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:48,080
Look, it is the new China now.

104
00:07:48,480 --> 00:07:49,560
But I am just worried.

105
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:51,560
I just want to go back and take a look.

106
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:54,200
Come.

107
00:07:54,440 --> 00:07:55,640
I will be generous this time

108
00:07:55,640 --> 00:07:57,040
and buy you a membership.

109
00:07:57,280 --> 00:07:58,440
Come.

110
00:07:59,640 --> 00:08:00,800
Come.

111
00:08:02,160 --> 00:08:04,880
You can watch everything in here for free.

112
00:08:14,280 --> 00:08:16,160
He is so stubborn.

113
00:08:18,480 --> 00:08:20,960
If you hadn't fooled him into thinking you could send him back,

114
00:08:20,960 --> 00:08:22,280
would he be so serious?

115
00:08:23,760 --> 00:08:25,290
What are you talking about?

116
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:27,080
You brought him back.

117
00:08:28,240 --> 00:08:29,280
For the membership today,

118
00:08:29,280 --> 00:08:30,680
we should split the bill.

119
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:32,200
Anyway, I paid the money.

120
00:08:33,400 --> 00:08:34,730
Little money-grubber.

121
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:36,360
Go to sleep.

122
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:41,799
Worrying about these things every day,

123
00:08:41,840 --> 00:08:43,880
my brain cells are almost dead.

124
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:57,240
After the outbreak of the full-scale War of Resistance,

125
00:08:57,240 --> 00:09:01,840
China's coastal ports were successively occupied or blockaded by the Japanese army.

126
00:09:01,840 --> 00:09:05,500
The hastily repaired Burma Road was in desperate need of drivers.

127
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:10,520
Finally, with the efforts of the patriotic overseas Chinese leader Tan Kah Kee,

128
00:09:10,520 --> 00:09:13,840
3,192 overseas Chinese living in Southeast Asia

129
00:09:14,440 --> 00:09:16,920
gave up their jobs and lives,

130
00:09:17,640 --> 00:09:19,400
said goodbye to their families,

131
00:09:19,400 --> 00:09:22,800
and resolutely embarked on the road to defend their country.

132
00:09:23,200 --> 00:09:25,120
It was at this time

133
00:09:25,640 --> 00:09:29,300
that they got a common name, Nanyang Overseas Chinese Mechanics.

134
00:09:30,360 --> 00:09:31,520
Push hard!

135
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:32,680
Let's go!

136
00:09:32,680 --> 00:09:36,000
Although they did not fight bloody battles with the enemy on the front line,

137
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:39,240
they also faced various life-and-death tests.

138
00:09:40,680 --> 00:09:43,140
Although they had no weapons in their hands,

139
00:09:43,560 --> 00:09:48,160
they provided an absolute guarantee for the War of Resistance for a period of time.

140
00:09:49,920 --> 00:09:51,650
Everywhere in the world today,

141
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:54,680
there are some octogenarians.

142
00:09:55,120 --> 00:09:57,800
They don't seem to be connected in any way,

143
00:09:58,160 --> 00:10:01,040
but during the War of Resistance against Japanese Aggression,

144
00:10:01,040 --> 00:10:04,400
they fought together in the same unit.

145
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:08,640
I sincerely swear

146
00:10:08,640 --> 00:10:12,720
to volunteer to join the Nanyang Overseas Chinese Mechanics Returning to Serve the Country,

147
00:10:12,720 --> 00:10:13,640
obey orders.

148
00:10:13,640 --> 00:10:16,160
In those extremely difficult years,

149
00:10:16,320 --> 00:10:18,520
they had a very resounding name,

150
00:10:19,040 --> 00:10:21,170
Nanyang Overseas Chinese Mechanics.

151
00:10:23,640 --> 00:10:28,960
The lifeline of the Burma Road built by the Nanyang Overseas Chinese Mechanics with their flesh and blood

152
00:10:28,960 --> 00:10:33,360
provided key strategic support for the final victory of the War of Resistance.

153
00:11:13,680 --> 00:11:17,280
What's wrong with this TV?

154
00:11:17,600 --> 00:11:18,400
What happened?

155
00:11:18,400 --> 00:11:19,600
It really went in.
